The paper discusses a framework for summarizing recent results in efficient and biologically plausible online training of recurrent neural networks. This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and specifically deals with neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of RNNs in control systems (cs.SY) and includes experiments on synthetic tasks that involve image processing (cs.CV).
